results.name: a(1) = 1; a(n+1) is the smallest number not already in the sequence which differs from a(n) at every digit.
link: Paul Tek, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 11 follows 20 as the smallest number not included earlier and differing at every digit position.
program: f u us = g us where
| and $ zipWith (/=) u v = (read v :: Int) : f v (delete v us)
